Barnes & Noble Surges Above $17-a-Share Buyout Offer From Liberty’s Malone

-- B y   C e c i l e   D a u r a t
-- 
2011-05-20T13:00:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-20/barnes-noble-surges-above-17-a-share-buyout-offer-from-liberty-s-malone.html
Barnes & Noble Inc. (BKS)  jumped 32 percent
to $18.60 in early trading, higher than the buyout offer from
John Malone’s Liberty Media Corp.  Liberty Media offered $17 a share, the bookstore chain said
in a statement yesterday. The shares rose $4.49 at 8:53 a.m.,
before the open of the New York Stock Exchange, after closing at
$14.11 yesterday.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Cecile Daurat at 
 cdaurat@bloomberg.net  